# AWS S3 Bucket Setup

## What I did:

- Created an S3 bucket in AWS
- Configured region and unique bucket name
- Kept Block Public Access enabled (default secure setting)
- Uploaded test files (text/image)

---

## Key Learnings:

- S3 bucket is a container for storing objects
- Buckets are private by default
- Each bucket name must be globally unique
- Data in S3 is highly durable and scalable

---

## Hands-on Summary:

- Created bucket: `anish-lab-bucket`
- Uploaded sample files
- Verified access via AWS console

---

## Mistakes to Avoid:

- Using non-unique bucket names
- Disabling security settings without understanding
- Uploading sensitive data without encryption

---

## Security Insight:

- Default private configuration prevents unauthorized access
- S3 is secure only if configured correctly

